President Obama announced his intent to nominate two individuals for key administration posts. The first is David J. Kappos, who is nominated for Under Secretary of Commerce for Intellectual Property and Director of the United States Patent and Trademark Office. Kappos is currently Vice President and Assistant General Counsel for Intellectual Property Law at IBM Corporation. He has extensive experience in intellectual property law and has served in various leadership positions in intellectual property law associations. The second nominee is Warren F. "Pete" Miller, Jr., who is nominated for Director of the Office of Civilian Radioactive Waste Management at the Department of Energy. Miller is a part-time professor at Texas A&M University and has a background in nuclear engineering. He has previously worked at Los Alamos National Laboratory and has been recognized for his contributions in the field. President Obama also announced his intention to nominate Miller for Assistant Secretary for Nuclear Energy at the Department of Energy.